Subject: fmha bwd: zero dq_acc for group/varlen deterministic mode

NeedsZeroDqAcc() gates whether the launcher zeroes the dq_acc workspace
before the backward kernels run. For non-persistent deterministic kernels it
only returned kHasMask, so group (varlen) mode with a non-causal padding mask
(the nmask kernel, kHasMask=false) left dq_acc unzeroed.

In group mode the deterministic reduction reads dq_acc split slots for
padded/masked KV that the main kernel never writes, so an unzeroed buffer
makes dq non-reproducible (and can yield NaN). Return kHasMask || kIsGroupMode
so group mode is always zeroed -- the same path that already covers causal
group mode via kHasMask.

diff --git a/3rdparty/composable_kernel/include/ck_tile/ops/fmha/kernel/fmha_bwd_kernel.hpp b/3rdparty/composable_kernel/include/ck_tile/ops/fmha/kernel/fmha_bwd_kernel.hpp
--- a/3rdparty/composable_kernel/include/ck_tile/ops/fmha/kernel/fmha_bwd_kernel.hpp
+++ b/3rdparty/composable_kernel/include/ck_tile/ops/fmha/kernel/fmha_bwd_kernel.hpp
@@ -222,9 +222,12 @@
         // non-deterministic and persistent kernels use atomic-add to write dq
         if constexpr(kUsePersistent || !kIsDeterministic)
             return true;
-        // Some block may be skipped with causal mask and dq are not set to zeros
-        // In these cases we need to zero out it first
-        return kHasMask;
+        // Non-persistent deterministic uses `set` (not atomic-add), but some dq_acc
+        // split slots are left unwritten and are still read during the reduction:
+        //  - causal mask skips tiles (kHasMask), and
+        //  - group/varlen mode leaves padded-KV splits untouched (kIsGroupMode).
+        // Zero those first so the reduction doesn't consume uninitialized memory.
+        return kHasMask || kIsGroupMode;
     }
 
